### Use this procedure to assign users to groups in Umbraco

**required objects:**

 - authorization: [this is the total code api information to authenticate with umbraco to process requests]
	- AppId (Guid)
	- ApiKey (Guid)
 - groups (string array) *an array of user group names
 - username (string) *user to be assigned to groups; example => myemail@email.com


#### Since the procedure is Json-Rpc, it must be wrapped with Json-Rpc objects

		{
			"method": <<Method Name>>,
			"params": <<parameters for the request>>,
			"id": <<id of the request>>
		}


#### Example		

		{
		    "method": "AssignUserGroups",
		    "params": {
		        "authorization": {
		            "AppId": "4d53bce03ec34c0a911182d4c228ee6c",
		            "ApiKey": "zYPSLb7uYA1NHFHtvZw+DGyqJr2P2/sT8puaAP+NFgs="
		        },
		        "groups": [
		            "Test 1",
		            "Test 2",
		            "Test 3"
		        ],
		        "username": "janedoe@outlook.com"
		    },
		    "id": 12
		}

### Returns confirmation of group assignment, with group ids

#### Example

		{
		    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
		    "result": {
		        "Message": "Groups assigned to user",
		        "TenantUid": null,
		        "Status": "Ok",
		        "Data": {
		            "Username": "janedoe@outlook.com",
		            "assignedGroups": "13,10,11,"
		        }
		    },
		    "id": 11
		}

## Possible Errors

		Unhandled = -999,
        UsernameDoesNotExist = 705,
        GroupDoesNotExist = 901

### Use this procedure to completely **DELETE** a tenant from Umbraco (including it's related objects)

**required objects:**

 - authorization: [this is the total code api information to authenticate with umbraco to process requests]
	- AppId (Guid)
	- ApiKey (Guid)
 - tenant:
	- TenantUid (Guid) example => "28d978f9-e9e1-4629-b246-97eec59b2493"
    - Username (string) *the user to be enabled, usually the main user; example => "bobdylan@outlook.com"
    - Group (string) *the group to be enabled, usually the main group; example => "Bob's Group"

#### Since the procedure is Json-Rpc, it must be wrapped with Json-Rpc objects

		{
			"method": <<Method Name>>,
			"params": <<parameters for the request>>,
			"id": <<id of the request>>
		}


#### Example			

		{
		    "method": "PurgeTenant",
		    "params": {
		        "authorization": {
		            "AppId": "4d53bce03ec34c0a911182d4c228ee6c",
		            "ApiKey": "zYPSLb7uYA1NHFHtvZw+DGyqJr2P2/sT8puaAP+NFgs="
		        },
		        "tenant": {
		            "TenantUid": "28d978f9-e9e1-4629-b246-97eec59b2493",
		            "Username": "bobdylan@outlook.com",
		            "Group": "Bob's Group"
		        }
		    },
		    "id": 99
		}

### Returns Confirmation of Tenant Removal, and Which objects were also removed

#### Example

		{
		    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
		    "result": {
		        "Message": "Tenant Purged from CMS",
		        "TenantUid": "28d978f9-e9e1-4629-b246-97eec59b2493",
		        "Status": "Ok",
		        "Data": {
		            "ContentFoundAndDeleted": true,
		            "GroupFoundAndDeleted": true,
		            "MediaFolderFoundAndDeleted": true,
		            "UserFoundAndDeleted": true
		        }
		    },
		    "id": 99
		}

## Possible Errors

		Unhandled = -999,
        TenantNotFound = 504,
        UsernameDoesNotExist = 705,
        GroupDoesNotExist = 901
